At the moment the password reset email has a generic link to the "forgotuserpassword" action above the button which says "Reset password". This is confusing a number of users as they are interpreting the generic link as the primary call to action as it is the first clickable thing in the email. This means I frequently receive emails from people saying "I clicked the link in the email but I just go back to the log in page", which I then subsequently have to inform them is the wrong link and that they should click the button instead.

My suggestion is that the text that says "This password reset request is valid for the next 24 hours. Don't worry you can always ask for a new password using the following link" should be moved below the "reset password" button.

